metadata.name: Reverberations #112
metadata.description:
[ CLICK TO START THE SOUND ]
Best viewed on a decent GPU for 60fps rendering
Play the instrument by clicking or touching the blobs
Supports any aspect ratio, however the resulting simulation will vary!

Everything in the universe is made up of vibrating energy, including us. Our thoughts and emotions are also vibrations of energy that influence the frequencies around us. 
Be kind.

Controls
[ click / touch ] - split blobs
[ /?play ] - query string to avoid automatic splits
[ s ] - save image
[ f ] - full screen

Created with Three.js + Rapier.js + Tone.js

metadata.name: Glitchy Masks #32
metadata.description:
A big thank you to Aleksandra from https://www.fxhash.xyz/u/Aleksandra for their assistance with the code!

In this project, I explored the concept of randomness and was pleasantly surprised by the results. After a few iterations, masks began to emerge. I added a mirroring effect to enhance the visual and added eyes for added realism. The end result is a series of intriguing masks, created through the use of randomness and artistic experimentation.

To save your canvas, simply press S.

For more information and to stay up to date with my work, follow me on Twitter at @lomzart or visit my portfolio website at lomz.net. Thank you for your interest!

metadata.name: Willie's Nightmare Cash Grab #11
metadata.description:
Through extensive lobbying, Disney helped change copyright law through the Copyright Term Extension Act to keep Mickey's earliest incarnation, Steamboat Willie, out of the public domain for an extra 20 years. While copyright law often protects artists, it shouldn't last forever. Thankfully, more hybridized forms of protection such as Creative Commons licenses have emerged allowing for protection as well as remixes and reimaginations. 

With Steamboat Willie now in the public domain, this collection builds upon Willie (and Disney's) nightmare of all sorts of off-brand chaos inflicted upon his form, transforming Mickey from an icon of family-friendly magic to one of nightmarish capitalism, sexual freedom, and murder run rampant. 

No commentary on the clash of capitalism and art would be complete without making this an open edition with a treasure hunt of trait pairings. The hunt will last as long as the open edition (two weeks), and after that, prizes shall be airdropped. 

For more information and to claim prizes, please join the House of Mors Discord: https://discord.gg/3N2KBfUuAN

Thanks to PureSpider for the image composition tool.

metadata.name: Moon Sun Ocean #250
metadata.description:
The secret to happiness is to simplify as much as possible. The details surrounding us must be said goodbye as soon as possible. The best thing we can do is to get started early and get rid of additional complexities as soon as possible. After that, we'll be able to breathe... After that, life will begin again!
There will be many words in this interpretation, despite its simplicity.
Made by p5.js
press 's' to save original size
